        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62495&amp;TOPIC_ID=7489&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Raid+Sugestions&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Kael is doable...search the web for "Kael Arena", there are some nice guides, complete with good maps of spawn points.  Here's a general info guide I wrote for my guild back when we did Kael.</P><P><b>KAEL DRAKKAL ARENA PRIMER</b></P><P><b><u>OUTSIDE THE ARENA</u></b><BR><b>Guard</b> or <b>Senior Guard:</b> up to 50th (melee)</P><P><b>Troopers:</b> Low 50s (melee, rampages) Most can be slowed no debuff. However some level 54 troopers are tough to slow no debuffs. Can rarely drop quest armor.</P><P><b>Adjutants:</b> 51-54 (priest, rampages, CH, Reckoning, etc.) Same as troopers. They rampage, gate and CH. Needs snare, they can run. Can drop quest armor.</P><P><b>Legionnaires:</b> 54ish (melee, rampages) Apply one MR debuff at least. They rampage. Hit in the 160+ range. Can drop quest armor.</P><P><b>Veterans:</b> 57 (melee, rampages, enrages) Apply Malosini. They are very resistant. They rampage and enrage. Hit for 220+ range. Can drop extremely rarely up to 3 pieces of armor.</P><P><b>Protectors of Zek:</b> 56 (priest version does same as Adjutants, rampage) Very easy to slow but apply debuff to make sure you slow it first shot, they hit in 330+ (priest version around 240) range so if they resist your slow, they will hurt you. Some are clerics, thus they CH/Gate. Needs to be snared, sometimes they don't gate but run. They can drop a nice blade called Defiance. The ones outside the arena are always priests.</P><P><b>Kallis Stormcaller:</b> 58 (melee, rampage, enrage) Hits like a runaway frieght train (he's a PoZ on steroids). Easy slow, same rule as protectors. Can drop Black Blade of Torment.</P><P><BR><b><u>INSIDE THE ARENA</u></b><BR><b>Bjrakor the Cold:</b> 55 (melee, rampage) hits in the 220+ range, can be slowed like legionaires, drops Gladiator Chain Legs or Sceptre of Mastery (very nice monk scepter). Can rampage.</P><P><b>Vealok the Angry:</b> 55 (melee, rampage) same as Bjrakor, drops Gladiator Chain Arms or the same monk scepter.</P><P><b>Semkak/Gkrean, Prophet of Vallon/Tallon:</b> 56-58 (priest, rampage, enrage, CH) Hits in 300ish, Heal, gate. Easy slow. Even if they resist, they will try to nuke you with uber cleric DD nukes so no real worry of melee. They CH, Gate, run. Drops are nice priest/caster gear but mostly Circlets of Vallon and Tallon.</P><P><b>Priest of Tallon/Vallon:</b> 54ish (same as Adjutants) Heal, CH, gate, run. Hit in the 200ish. Easy slow.</P><P><b>Cleric of Tallon/Vallon:</b> same as Priests of Tallon/Vallon</P><P><b>Frost Giant Gladiator:</b> Same as Troopers</P><P><b>Storm Giant Gladiator:</b> Same as Legionnaires</P><P><b>Protectors of Zek:</b> 56 (priest version does same as Adjutants, Melee version can rarely enrage, both rampage) priest max hit at 240ish, melee 360.</P><P><BR><b><u>DROPS</u></b><BR><b>Troopers, Adjutants, Legionnaires, Veterans:</b> (not a compete list)<BR>Various armor pieces needed for Thurgadin Quest armors<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4567" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4567</a>]Velium Swiftblade[/link] (1hs - shows) Dmg 5, Dly 24, Effect: Haste  Ra P Sk B Ro Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4416" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4416</a>]Thunder Runed Dagger[/link] (shows - ND) Dmg 9, Dly 18. +3 Int +4 vsMg +30 Mana   Wz Mg E N<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4448" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4448</a>]Thunder Runed War Spear[/link] (shows) Dmg 13, Dly 33. +5 AC +5 vsMg +25 HP   Ra Sm Sk B Ro Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4192" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4192</a>]Thunder Runed Great Sword[/link] (2hs - shows - ND) Dmg 29, Dly 41. +7 vsMg, Proc: Strike of Thunder (375 damage in 3 waves AoE Rain)   Sk Wr P<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4129" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4129</a>]Silvery Belt of Contention[/link] +10 AC +4 Sta +5 Wis +5 Int Effect: Haste, All/all<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4488" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4488</a>]Thunder Etched Gauntlets[/link] +20 AC +6 Str +4 Wis +4 Int +2 vsMg +1 vsFire/Cold/Pos/Dis   C P Sk<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4729" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4729</a>]White Bear Pelt Cloak[/link] +11 AC +5 Str +5 Wis +3 vsMg +75 HP +50 Mana P<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4779" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4779</a>]Black Bear Pelt Cloak[/link] +11 AC +5 Str +5 Int +3 vsMg +75 HP +50 Mana Sk<BR>Boots of Dark Passage  	+17 AC +10 vsMg +7 vsDis +55 HP +15 Mana   Sk<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5610" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5610</a>]Sickly Glowing Orb[/link] +5 Sta -10 vsCold +60 HP   N E Mg Wz<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4225" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4225</a>]Velium War Mask[/link] +2 AC +4 Wis +4 Int +25 Mana   N E Mg Wz Sm D C</P><P><b>Protectors of Zek:</b> (can also drop things from the Vet loot table)<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4318" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4318</a>]Defiance[/link] (shows - 1hs) Dmg 9, Dly 19. +10 AC +6 Str +8 Dex Ra P Sk B Ro Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4518" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4518</a>]Hammer of Rage[/link] (shows - 2hb) Dmg 30, Dly 46, Proc: Yaulp, Ra Sm C P Sk Wr<BR>The two protectors next to Kallis always drop their head (used for PoG ranger quest along with Kallis' head)</P><P><b>Kallis Stormcaller:</b> <BR>Kallis' head (always) For the Ranger PoG quest (Helm of Ugliness)<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4500" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4500</a>]Black Blade of Tormenting[/link] (rare, shows) Dmg 9, Dly 22.  Proc: Torment (Ra Sk B Ro Wr) [Torment: procs at level 46, 20dd + 50 DoT over 5 ticks - MASSIVE taunt]</P><P><b>Bjrakor the Cold:</b><BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4319" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4319</a>]Gladiator Chain Leggings[/link] (common - ND) +17 AC +2 Str +6 Wis +4 Cha +10 vsMg +20 HP   Ra Sm D C P Sk B Ro Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4753" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4753</a>]Scepter of Mastery[/link] (rare, shows - ND) Dmg 13, Dly 21. +6 Sta +6 Agi   (Mk)</P><P><b>Vealok the Angry:</b><BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4320" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4320</a>]Gladiator Chain Sleeves[/link] (common - ND) +16 AC +9 Str +5 Dex +3 vsMg +2 vsFire +2 vsCold +2 vsPos +2 vsDis +20 HP   Ra Sm D C P Sk B Ro Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4321" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4321</a>]Runed Frost Blade[/link] (rare, shows) Dmg 34, Dly 49. +15 vsCold +75 HP   P Sk Wr</P><P><b>Semkak, Prophet of Vallon:</b> <BR>Idol of Disease (always has) for some PoG Tunare quest,<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4451" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4451</a>]Steel Wristband of Strategy[/link] (uncommon), +2 AC +7 Str +7 Dex +7 Int -5 Cha  (N E Mg Wz)<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4482" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4482</a>]Circlet of Vallon[/link] (rare), +18 AC +9 vsMg +9 vsFire +9 vsDis (All/All)<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4572" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4572</a>]Book of Strategy[/link] (rare, range slot) +6 Str +6 Wis (All/All)</P><P><b>Gkrean, Prophet of Tallon:</b><BR>Idol of Corruption (always has) for some PoG quest,<BR>Teachings of Gkrean (always has) - Raglyn's Promise (Circlet of Falinkan) Quest<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4062" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4062</a>]Gauntlets of Iron Tactics[/link] (uncommon) +2 AC +7 Str +7 Dex +7 Wis -5 Cha<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4546" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4546</a>]Circlet of Tallon[/link] (rare - ND), +18 AC +9 vsMg +9 vsCold +9 vsPos   (All)</P><P><BR><b><u>OTHER KAEL NOTABLES</u></b><BR><b>Sentinels</b> (Tormax area only): Extremely resistant (red con to 60), usually need ToV like debuff to slow them. AFAIK, red cons to 60 rampage only, blue cons flurry and both enrage. Hard to solo pull, have 2 tanks with defensive ready they hit in the 220+ and extremely fast. Some are level 60 shaman buffed by Kyenka near Tormax. Can drop up to 3 pieces of quest armor.  Usually it's 2.</P><P><b>Gleed Dragonhunter</b> (near Tormax): Level 55. Drops a RNG/WAR bow and a ranger blade. Hits for 200ish, easy slow, needs to be snared.<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3990" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3990</a>]Bow of the Huntsman[/link] (ND) Dmg 20, Dly 30. Range 180, Proc: Spirit Strike (81dd), Ra Wr<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3992" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3992</a>]Flamesong[/link] (1hs - rare) Dmg 10, Dly 24.  +6 Wis, Proc: Flame Song (75dd), Ra</P><P><b>Dlammaz Stormslayer</b> (near Tormax): Hits for 520+ (double), has mega HP (about 80k), can be slowed but not easy. PH for "a storm giant warlord" who drops the Mask of War. Have a tank with defensive tank him until you slow him. You need multiple groups take him out. Only a small step down from Tormax himself...badest man in the village.<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3998" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3998</a>]Cloak of the Maelstrom[/link] +11 AC +3 Str +6 Sta +10 Dex +5 Int +55 HP, All/All<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4851" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4851</a>]Frostbringer[/link] (1hs) Dmg 12, Dly 22. +7 AC, Proc: Frostbite(60dd, 15AC debuff for 10 ticks)  Ra P Sk Wr</P><P><b>Captain Bvellos</b> (in bank): He's a major undercon.  Doesn't hit all that hard, but has a seemingly bottomless number of hps.  Hard to separate from Drioc, and Drioc can heal him.<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3803" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3803</a>]Glowing Black Sword[/link] (common) 1hs - Dmg 9, Dly 22. +20 Dex, Proc: Dispell, Ra Sk B Ro Wr [proc effects the wielder - level 30]<BR>[link=<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3885" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3885</a>]Glimmering Mythril Torque[/link] (rare) +15 AC +2 Str, Wr</P><P><b>Staff Sgt. Drioc</b> (in bank): Priest mob.<BR>Sgt. Drioc's Head (always has) - Raglyn's Promise (Circlet of Falinkan) Quest</P><P><b>Derakor the Vindicator (Vindi):</b> Temple area behind the arena (behind<BR>Kallis).  Unslowable, doubles for 700, Enrage, Rampage.  Approximately 120k<BR>hps.  Requires a CH chain and good aggro management.<BR>Derakor's Head (always has) - PoG Gloves of Earthcrafting quest.<BR>Boots of the Vindicator +30 AC +5 Sta +5 Wis +5 Int +13 vsDis +50 HP   (Sm C P Sk B Wr)<BR>Chestplate of Vindication  +45 AC +15 Sta +15 vsMg +15 vsFire +15 vsCold +15 vsPos +15 vsDis +100 HP   (Wr B Sk P C Sm)<BR>Living Thunder Earring +10 AC +9 Str, +10 vsM, Effect: See Invisible (ALL/ALL)</P><P></P><P><b><u>GENERAL INFO</u></b><BR>The spawn timer is 30 minutes.</P><P>The arena is generally considered 2 camps. One camp on each side, left and right when a camp check is called out. Most groups set up at the spawn point of the Guard/Senior Guard roamer, since nothing else wanders there and it leaves a fairly nice area for fighting.</P><P>Do not push mobs over the small wall at the usual camp area... there are mobs below that will agro and train up to you.</P><P>Do not push mobs towards the opposite wall near the ramp, if Gkrean or Semkak is up, he and his lackeys will Complete Heal any giants that need it if you get to close to their wall.</P><P>Remember Giants will switch targets when they see someone is below two bars of life if you are high enough on the agro list.</P><P>Adjutants, Protectors and the named mobs all hate having Tashan cast on them. They seem to agro faster than most mobs, so I suggest not casting it til they are down a ways on life.</P><P>Pathing is messed up around the entry ramp. If you pull a mob to or down the ramp, it gets near the ramp, and paths back into the camp corner before running to and down the ramp. This means if anyone pulls mobs down the ramp while your group is at the camp corner, you might end up having adds if the giant wasnt agroed enough. This also means that when pulling the area to enter the arena you will almost always get more than one (unless you can time the pull right - when the roamer is away).</P><P>When splitting mobs like the 3 Protectors of Zek in the temple area, use the pillars outside or the walls to your advantage. You can agro them and if you are fast enough, run to the side where they must path thru the wall to get you, sometimes they warp to you one at a time and it allows you to FD and let a tagger get them.  <b>Note:</b> rumor has it that PoZ can be single pulled every time by a bard using lull song.</P><P>When pulling Bjrakor and Vealok, if you run up the ramp and out the door fast enough, you can get them to sometime warp to you singly. This also works with Semkak and Gkrean.</P><P>Beware when pulling Gkrean and Semkaks rooms, Bjrakor and Vealok can sometimes agro you when you go down the stairs into the priests room.</P><P>Some of the named mobs in this area will have their placeholders despawn after a certain amount of time (I think 6-8 hours) and the named mob will spawn in its place. The placeholders can be killed and force a spawn on the named guys.</P><P><BR><b><u>SPECIAL INFO FOR TRACKERS</u></b><BR>Rangers/Druids should check tracking for a couple of special spawns:</P><P><b>Capt. Bvellos:</b> In the bank.  Drops a nice WAR neck and a "nice" sword (see above). Fairly common spawn.</P><P><b>Oracle Bloodstorm:</b> In the Icehouse.  Rare spawn oracle that drops the Rune Etched Icewurm Fang, an exceptional Shaman piercer.</P><P><b>a storm giant warlord:</b> Between the Bank and Tormax areas. Placeholder for Dlammaz Stormslayer.  The Warlord drops the Mask of War, a WIS face piece.</P><P>Edit: Bah!  Phooie, this board handles links different than EZBoard...the formatting is a little whacky.</P><P><BR>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Children of the Phoenix (Tunare)</P><P>Edited by - Nergal on 08/23/2002  13:42:45<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
