         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Here is another question though, How many people would be too much and how many people would be too little?<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>Really depends on what you want to do in Kael and who you have with you.  When my guild still did Kael, we took two groups of mid-50s and we could handle everything in the arena, including Protectors and Kallis.  We farmed armor and generally had a good time.  I've also been on Kael raids with 11 groups...and that was mind bogglingly boring, but the kill rate was rather impressive.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>I know Kael can be done by one grp of high 40's low 50's but wasn't sure about the arena.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>A single group of high 40s, low 50s isn't going to get far in the arena.  Veterans can spawn in there, and they're around level 57 with 20-22k hit points.  That's a pretty tough nut the crack for a single low level group.</P><P>The group you stated you'd be leading (2-3 groups, 40s-50s) should be ok in the arena.  I'd expect it to be quite challenging actually.  If possible I would suggest trying to find a 55+ warrior (defensive is handy, but you can do ok without it), and definately the highest level shaman you can.  Some of those giants hit damned hard, you want them slowed.</P><P>Now a word about drop rates in Kael...don't go expecting to get any Thurg armor.  It's almost a myth.  The drops rates are well below poor...bordering on non-existant.  One giant in 30 might drop something.</P><P>It's all about perspective.  If you go expecting a challenging night doing something new with friends, you'll have a lot of fun.  If you go to farm armor, you're going to be very dissappointed.</P><P></P><P>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Children of the Phoenix (Tunare)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
