        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Nice Guide, Nergal!</P><P>Some other notes re: Kael arena</P><P>Protectors of Zek summon.  If a first tash/slow attempt fails, the Chanter/Shaman will probably be summonned (and killed) on the second try if cast too soon.</P><P>There is (or was ~6 months ago) a bug with the spawning of the Idol of Zek.  I don't know enough about Kael to know how or why, but it can warp into the arena and wipe an unprepaired or uncapable raid, and then sit there camping the wiped raid.  My shammy's guild once wiped there when the IoZ warped in.  Our raid was a 5-6 group 45 to low-50s with lots of tanks but weak on casters and healers.  A GM was nice enough to poof it for us at the time so we could rez, but the 60 minute wait pretty much screwed the raid.  </P><P>Watch the push back on the higher-HP giants.  It's easy enough to push em over the wall and aggro the mobs below.  Have the raid leaders work with the tanks (and clerics) to have a plan for how to turn 'em around when they get close to the wall.</P><P>PS -- Nergal put double quotes around the url after the LINK=.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310159" target="_blank">Gunkk</a><BR>46 Iksar Necro<BR>The Nameless<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

