        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Protectors of Zek summon.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>Everything except possibly the lowest level guards summons.  The Arena is a good place to learn the basics of aggro control.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>There is (or was ~6 months ago) a bug with the spawning of the Idol of Zek.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>To the best of my knowledge that has been fixed...at least I haven't heard of it happening recently.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Watch the push back on the higher-HP giants. It's easy enough to push em over the wall and aggro the mobs below.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>You definately want to pull mobs back to the corner, then hook and pin then into the wall.  Have the MA bury a shoulder in the wall and all the melees form an arc pushing the mob into the wall.  From that position it's relatively simple to keep the giant where you want him by having the MA switch sides...though you shouldn't have a lot of push like that.</P><P>The giants that cast you want to treat a differently...those you want to push around as much as possible.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>PS -- Nergal put double quotes around the url after the LINK=.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>Bah!  I'm far to lazy to go re-edit all those links.  It was originally formatted for an EZBoard :)</P><P></P><P>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Children of the Phoenix (Tunare)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif